               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾāmra Māryām “Miracles of Mary” (fols. 3ra-54ra)&#xD;
I-1) Maṣḥafa śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols. 3ra-7va)&#xD;
I-2) Introductory exhortation (fols. 7ra-10vb)&#xD;
I-3) ʾƎsaggǝd laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki … “I worship Thee…” (fols. 10vb-12rb)&#xD;
I-4) Taʾāmra Māryām: 29 partly numbered miracles (fols. 12rb-53rb, 54ra)&#xD;
I-5) ʾAkkonu bǝʾǝsi… “Does not the man…” (distributed among the miracles of Mary, fols. 15rb-52vb)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl ba-kǝlʾe Māryām ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus kahāli … "O my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, mother of Jesus the Almighty ..." (<locus target="9rb">9rb-</locus>va),</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām dǝngǝl ʾǝmma bǝrhān wa-ʾǝmma nädd... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Virgin Mary, Mother of the Light and Mother of the Flame ..." (<locus from="9va" to="10vb">9va-10vb</locus>).</note>
                     <note>Some miracles are not numbered. The first miracle is followed by the hymn: Sobä ṣäḥafä Däqsǝyos täʾamriha ʿǝludä ... "When Däqsǝyos wrote the collection of her miracles ..." (<locus target="14va">14va</locus>).</note>
                     <note>Text I-5 comprises 25 strophes which are strophes 2-10, 12-27 according to GrohHymn pp. 336-53.</note>
                  </msItem>
